definition.value: Any of various changes which take place after death.

A process in which the skin and flesh of a corpse can be preserved. The process can occur either naturally, or it can be intentional. If it occurs naturally, it is the result of cold (as can be found in a glacier), acid (as can be found in a bog) or dryness. The Ancient Egyptians wrapped bandages around the corpse to protect the body from rotting.
Mummification which takes place intentionally, such as that observed among Ancient Egyptians.
Any of various natural processes which cause mummification, such as extreme cold, high aridity, or lack of oxygen.
